  <heading>Condominiums and Cooperatives: Income Eligibility</heading>
  <section>
    <prefix>Regulation</prefix>
    <num>.01</num>
    <heading>Income Eligibility Figures Applicable to Condominium Conversions in Maryland.</heading>
    <para>
      <num>A.</num>
      <text>Pursuant to the provisions of the <cite doc="Md. Code" path="grp|11-137">Real Property Article, §11-137, Annotated Code of Maryland</cite>, and <cite doc="Md. Code" path="gca|5-6">Corporations and Associations Article, §5-6</cite>B-07, income eligibility figures have been prepared to assist in the determination of "designated households" within the meaning of these sections.</text>
    </para>
    <para>
      <num>B.</num>
      <text>A county or incorporated municipality which is located within a Standard Metropolitan Statistical Area (SMSA) may, by ordinance or resolution, adopt the income eligibility figure applicable to the county or to the SMSA.</text>
    </para>
    <annotations/>
  </section>
